# File: tests/features/setup.feature
#
# Generated from: specs/feature-vault-setup/requirements.md
# Issue: #9

Feature: Vault setup skill
  As a Claude Code + Obsidian power user
  I want a single one-time command that points obsidian-memory at my vault
  So that every future Claude Code session on every project benefits from vault-backed memory

  Background:
    Given a scratch HOME at "$BATS_TEST_TMPDIR/home"
    And a scratch Obsidian vault at "$BATS_TEST_TMPDIR/vault"

  # --- Happy Path ---

  Scenario: First-run setup against a real vault
    Given no file exists at "$HOME/.claude/obsidian-memory/config.json"
    When the user runs "/obsidian-memory:setup $VAULT"
    Then "$HOME/.claude/obsidian-memory/config.json" exists
    And its "vaultPath" field equals "$VAULT"
    And its "rag.enabled" field is true
    And its "distill.enabled" field is true
    And "$VAULT/claude-memory/sessions/" is a directory
    And "$VAULT/claude-memory/projects" is a symlink pointing at "$HOME/.claude/projects"
    And "$VAULT/claude-memory/Index.md" exists
    And "$VAULT/claude-memory/Index.md" contains "# Claude Memory Index"
    And "$VAULT/claude-memory/Index.md" contains "## Sessions"

  # --- Idempotency ---

  Scenario: Re-running setup is a no-op
    Given setup has already completed successfully against "$VAULT"
    And "$HOME/.claude/obsidian-memory/config.json" has an extra user key "notes.enabled" set to true
    When the user runs "/obsidian-memory:setup $VAULT" a second time
    Then the "vaultPath" field still equals "$VAULT"
    And the "notes.enabled" user key is still true
    And "$VAULT/claude-memory/Index.md" is unchanged from the previous run
    And "$VAULT/claude-memory/projects" still points at "$HOME/.claude/projects"

  # --- Error Handling ---

  Scenario: Vault path does not exist
    Given the path "$BATS_TEST_TMPDIR/no-such-vault" does not exist
    When the user runs "/obsidian-memory:setup $BATS_TEST_TMPDIR/no-such-vault"
    Then setup reports that the vault path does not exist
    And "$HOME/.claude/obsidian-memory/config.json" was not created
    And no directory was created under "$BATS_TEST_TMPDIR/no-such-vault"

  Scenario: "projects" exists as a non-symlink
    Given "$VAULT/claude-memory/projects" is a regular directory (not a symlink)
    And "$VAULT/claude-memory/projects/user-file.md" exists
    When the user runs "/obsidian-memory:setup $VAULT"
    Then setup refuses to delete "$VAULT/claude-memory/projects"
    And "$VAULT/claude-memory/projects/user-file.md" still exists
    And setup prints a message instructing the user to move or remove it manually
    And "$HOME/.claude/obsidian-memory/config.json" was still created

  # --- Alternative Paths ---

  Scenario: Stale symlink is atomically repointed
    Given "$VAULT/claude-memory/projects" is a symlink pointing at "/tmp/stale"
    When the user runs "/obsidian-memory:setup $VAULT"
    Then "$VAULT/claude-memory/projects" now points at "$HOME/.claude/projects"
    And no user data under "$VAULT" was deleted

  Scenario: Optional MCP registration on opt-in
    Given the user answers "Yes" to the MCP registration prompt
    When the user runs "/obsidian-memory:setup $VAULT"
    Then the command "claude mcp add -s user obsidian --transport websocket ws://localhost:22360" was invoked
    And a non-zero exit from "claude mcp add" is reported as non-fatal

  Scenario: Optional MCP registration on skip
    Given the user answers "Skip" to the MCP registration prompt
    When the user runs "/obsidian-memory:setup $VAULT"
    Then the command "claude mcp add" was not invoked
    And setup still completes the filesystem steps

  # --- Edge Case ---

  Scenario: Missing deps at setup time
    Given "jq" is not on PATH
    And "claude" is not on PATH
    When the user runs "/obsidian-memory:setup $VAULT"
    Then "$HOME/.claude/obsidian-memory/config.json" was still created
    And "$VAULT/claude-memory/sessions/" still exists
    And the final report lists "jq" and "claude" as missing
    And setup exits successfully
